description: Olympic bronze medalist Bajrang Punia received a four-year ban from NADA for allegedly refusing a dope test. Punia denies the refusal, claiming NADA used expired kits. He believes the ban is retaliation for his protest against former WFI president Brij Bhushan Sharan Singh and his affiliation with the Congress party.
title: 'If I join BJP, my bans will be lifted': Bajrang Punia on NADA suspension

description: Shashi Tharoor disagreed with his party's view on electronic voting machines. He defended the machines but worried about potential misuse in elections.  Tharoor suggested the Election Commission should address these concerns.  Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge wants paper ballots.  The BJP won big in Maharashtra, while the opposition struggled.
title: 'Not machines, but machinery': Tharoor differs from Kharge on EVMs

description: The US Embassy in Pakistan warned citizens about a potential threat to the Serena Hotel in Peshawar.  They were told to avoid the hotel and surrounding area until December 16, 2024.  A "Do Not Travel" advisory remains in effect for Khyber Pakhtunkhwa province due to terrorism.  Clashes between tribes in northwest Pakistan resulted in casualties, highlighting the volatile security situation.
title: US warns Americans against travel to Pakistan

description: Manipur Police intensified security measures, establishing 94 checkpoints and conducting searches following recent violence in Jiribam.  Mobile internet suspension extended, while a protest demands the return of a missing man within three days. The NIA has taken over three major cases related to the violence.
title: Manipur violence: 94 checkpoints installed, search ops on in Jiribam

description: Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) chairman Mohsin Naqvi insists on equal treatment from India regarding the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy, slated for Pakistan. Naqvi firmly stated Pakistan will refuse to play in India if India doesn't reciprocate. He emphasized ongoing discussions with the ICC and the need for fairness.
title: 'Not acceptable that Pakistan play in India, and they don't play here'
ED team attacked while conducting raids in Delhi; FIR lodged

description: Cricket legend Wasim Akram analyzes Jasprit Bumrah's unique bowling style during his commentary on the Border-Gavaskar Trophy.  Akram highlights Bumrah's unusual wrist action and extended release point, contributing to the ball's skid and surprising batsmen.  This analysis follows Bumrah's impressive 8/72 match figures, leading India to a resounding victory against Australia in the first Test.
title: WATCH: Wasim Akram explains why Jasprit Bumrah is a terror with the ball

description: Former US President Donald Trump claimed Mexico's new President, Claudia Sheinbaum Pardo, agreed to halt migration to the US during a phone call. Pardo clarified Mexico's approach focuses on managing migration within its borders, not closing them. Trump also mentioned discussing drug trafficking, while threatening tariffs on Mexican imports to combat drugs and illegal immigration.
title: 'Stop flow of illegal immigrants': Trump vs Mexico President on border plans

description: The Delhi High Court questioned the Delhi government's rejection of the Ayushman Bharat health scheme. BJP MPs filed a PIL seeking the scheme's implementation. The court expressed concern over the state of Delhi's hospitals and lack of funds. The court highlighted the refusal of central aid despite the dire situation. The scheme offers Rs 5 lakh health coverage.
title: 'We are shocked': Hospitals ‘in mess’, strange Delhi govt refusing aid, observes HC

description: Nvidia's stock is on watch.  Citi predicts a potential 27% jump to $175. CEO Jensen Huang's CES 2025 keynote is key.  He will discuss the "Blackwell" AI chip.  New robotics and industrial applications will be revealed.  Profit margins are expected to rise.  Nvidia powers humanoid robots. The company's stock has surged 176% this year.
title: Nvidia put on 90 days 'watch' by Citi analysts: ‘Big announcement' on Jan 6, & more

description: A legal battle has erupted between actors Dhanush and Nayanthara over footage used in the Netflix documentary 'Nayanthara: Beyond The Fairy Tale'. Dhanush has filed a civil suit against Nayanthara, her husband Vignesh Shivan, and their production house for using clips from the film 'Naanum Rowdy Dhaan' without his permission. Dhanush's legal team is also pursuing action against Netflix's Mumbai affiliates. Nayanthara publicly addressed Dhanush, accusing him of harboring vengeance and highlighting the struggles she faced as a self-made woman in the film industry.
title: Madras HC demands Nayanthara's response in civil suit filed by Dhanush

description: Multiple members of Donald Trump's incoming administration were targeted with bomb threats and swatting incidents, including a pipe bomb threat with a pro-Palestinian message. Elise Stefanik, Matt Gaetz, Lori Chavez-DeRemer, and Lee Zeldin were among those targeted. Zeldin confirmed a pipe bomb threat against his family.
title: 'Violent, UnAmerican': Bomb and swatting threats against Trump's cabinet picks
IT hiring expected to grow by 10-12% in 6 months: Report

description: Indonesia rejected Apple's $100 million investment proposal, deeming it insufficient.  The government demands increased local manufacturing and a larger investment, similar to Apple's investment in Vietnam, before lifting the ban on iPhone 16 sales.  Indonesia seeks further negotiations and a more substantial commitment from Apple for 2024-2026, including a potential manufacturing plant.
title: 'Indonesia refuses to remove ban on iPhone 16 series; we need a ...': Minister

description: An Indian-American group urged US leaders to investigate attacks on minorities in Bangladesh. The group fears Bangladesh is becoming a radicalized state. They highlighted the imprisonment of Chinmoy Krishna Das and over 200 attacks on Hindu temples. Das was denied bail after arrest. Protests erupted in several cities.
title: Indian-American body urges Biden, Trump to act on B'desh minority attacks

description: President-elect Donald Trump announced a 25% tariff on goods from Mexico and Canada, and a 10% tariff on Chinese imports.  The tariffs, aimed at curbing illegal immigration and fentanyl flow, drew criticism, particularly regarding Canada's inclusion.  Elon Musk commented that fentanyl prices would likely increase as a result.
title: Why Donald Trump is imposing tariff on US' close ally Canada
6.7 lakh SIM cards 'linked with cybercrimes' blocked: Govt

description: Liverpool triumphed 2-0 over Real Madrid in a Champions League clash, becoming the only team with a perfect record this season. Despite Mbappe's missed penalty, Liverpool secured victory with goals from MacAllister and Gakpo. Elsewhere, Dortmund won 3-0, while Aston Villa's late goal was disallowed. Monaco lost a thriller to Benfica, and Lille edged Bologna.
title: Champions League: Liverpool beat Real Madrid 2-0 to go top

description: A Hindu group, Hindu Sena, has filed a lawsuit claiming the Ajmer dargah was built over a Shiva temple. They cite a 1911 book and seek an ASI survey, echoing the Gyanvapi and Krishna Janmabhoomi disputes. The Ajmer court issued notices to the government and ASI, with the next hearing set for December 20th.
title: Petition claims temple beneath Ajmer Sharif; court notice to govt, ASI

description: Prithvi Shaw's cricketing career has taken a hit. He was not picked by any team at the IPL 2025 auction.  His former coach revealed concerns about Shaw's work ethic and discipline.  Shaw's poor form and disciplinary issues led to his exclusion from the Mumbai Ranji team.  He was once considered a rising star but now faces an uncertain future.
title: 'Yashasvi ne...': Ex-coach explains why Prithvi went unsold at IPL Auction

description: Following a significant defeat in the Maharashtra assembly polls, the Shiv Sena (UBT) is contemplating contesting upcoming civic and local body elections independently. Party MLAs and functionaries have urged Uddhav Thackeray to lead this solo campaign, particularly in previously dominant areas.
title: Post-poll drubbing: Go solo in local body polls, UBT netas tell Uddhav
